 141 ExpressionBinder::ExpressionBinder(const Span& span_, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit_, BoundFunction* boundFunction_, ContainerScope* containerScope_, StatementBinder* statementBinder_, bool lvalue_) :
 142     span(span_), boundCompileUnit(boundCompileUnit_), symbolTable(boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable()), module(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule()), 
 143     boundFunction(boundFunction_), containerScope(containerScope_), statementBinder(statementBinder_), lvalue(lvalue_), inhibitCompile(false)
 144 {
 145 }
 146 
 147 void ExpressionBinder::BindUnaryOp(BoundExpression* operand, Node& node, const std::u32string& groupName)
 148 {
 149     std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> arguments;
 150     arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(operand));
 151     std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
 152     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
 153     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, operand->GetType()->BaseType()->ClassOrNsScope()));
 154     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
 155     std::vector<TypeSymbol*> templateArgumentTypes;
 156     std::unique_ptr<Exception> exception;
 157     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> operatorFunCall = ResolveOverload(groupName, containerScope, functionScopeLookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, boundFunction, node.GetSpan(), 
 158         OverloadResolutionFlags::dontThrow, templateArgumentTypes, exception);
 159     if (!operatorFunCall)
 160     {
 161         if (arguments[0]->GetType()->PlainType(node.GetSpan())->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 162         {
 163             if (arguments[0]->GetType()->IsReferenceType())
 164             {
 165                 TypeSymbol* type = arguments[0]->GetType()->RemoveReference(node.GetSpan())->AddPointer(node.GetSpan());
 166                 arguments[0].reset(new BoundReferenceToPointerExpression(module, std::move(arguments[0]), type));
 167             }
 168             else
 169             {
 170                 TypeSymbol* type = arguments[0]->GetType()->PlainType(node.GetSpan())->AddPointer(node.GetSpan());
 171                 arguments[0].reset(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(arguments[0]), type));
 172             }
 173             operatorFunCall = std::move(ResolveOverload(groupName, containerScope, functionScopeLookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, boundFunction, node.GetSpan()));
 174         }
 175         else
 176         {
 177             throw *exception;
 178         }
 179     }
 180     CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), operatorFunCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
 181     LocalVariableSymbol* temporary = nullptr;
 182     if (operatorFunCall->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnsClassInterfaceOrClassDelegateByValue())
 183     {
 184         TypeSymbol* type = operatorFunCall->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType();
 185         temporary = boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->CreateTemporary(type, node.GetSpan());
 186         operatorFunCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary)), 
 187             type->AddPointer(node.GetSpan()))));
 188         if (type->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 189         {
 190             ClassTypeSymbol* classType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(type);
 191             if (classType->Destructor())
 192             {
 193                 std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> destructorCall(new BoundFunctionCall(module, span, classType->Destructor()));
 194                 destructorCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(operatorFunCall->Arguments().back()->Clone()));
 195                 boundFunction->AddTemporaryDestructorCall(std::move(destructorCall));
 196             }
 197         }
 198     }
 199     expression.reset(operatorFunCall.release());
 200     if (temporary)
 201     {
 202         expression.reset(new BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression(module, std::move(expression),      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary))));
 203         expression->SetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::bindToRvalueReference);
 204     }
 205 }
 206 
 207 void ExpressionBinder::BindUnaryOp(UnaryNode& unaryNode, const std::u32string& groupName)
 208 {
 209     unaryNode.Subject()->Accept(*this);
 210     BoundExpression* operand = expression.release();
 211     BindUnaryOp(operand, unaryNode, groupName);
 212 }
 213 
 214 void ExpressionBinder::BindBinaryOp(BinaryNode& binaryNode, const std::u32string& groupName)
 215 {
 216     binaryNode.Left()->Accept(*this);
 217     BoundExpression* left = expression.release();
 218     binaryNode.Right()->Accept(*this);
 219     BoundExpression* right = expression.release();
 220     BindBinaryOp(left, right, binaryNode, groupName);
 221 }
 222 
 223 void ExpressionBinder::BindBinaryOp(BoundExpression* left, BoundExpression* right, Node& node, const std::u32string& groupName)
 224 {
 225     std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> arguments;
 226     arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(left));
 227     arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(right));
 228     std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
 229     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
 230     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, left->GetType()->BaseType()->ClassOrNsScope()));
 231     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, right->GetType()->BaseType()->ClassOrNsScope()));
 232     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
 233     std::vector<TypeSymbol*> templateArgumentTypes;
 234     std::unique_ptr<Exception> exception;
 235     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> operatorFunCall = ResolveOverload(groupName, containerScope, functionScopeLookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, boundFunction, node.GetSpan(), 
 236         OverloadResolutionFlags::dontThrow, templateArgumentTypes, exception);
 237     if (!operatorFunCall)
 238     {
 239         if (arguments[0]->GetType()->PlainType(node.GetSpan())->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 240         {
 241             if (arguments[0]->GetType()->IsReferenceType())
 242             {
 243                 TypeSymbol* type = arguments[0]->GetType()->RemoveReference(node.GetSpan())->AddPointer(node.GetSpan());
 244                 arguments[0].reset(new BoundReferenceToPointerExpression(module, std::move(arguments[0]), type));
 245             }
 246             else
 247             {
 248                 TypeSymbol* type = arguments[0]->GetType()->PlainType(node.GetSpan())->AddPointer(node.GetSpan());
 249                 arguments[0].reset(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(arguments[0]), type));
 250             }
 251             operatorFunCall = std::move(ResolveOverload(groupName, containerScope, functionScopeLookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, boundFunction, node.GetSpan()));
 252         }
 253         else
 254         {
 255             throw *exception;
 256         }
 257     }
 258     CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), operatorFunCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
 259     LocalVariableSymbol* temporary = nullptr;
 260     if (operatorFunCall->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnsClassInterfaceOrClassDelegateByValue())
 261     {
 262         TypeSymbol* type = operatorFunCall->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType();
 263         temporary = boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->CreateTemporary(type, node.GetSpan());
 264         operatorFunCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary)), 
 265             type->AddPointer(node.GetSpan()))));
 266         if (type->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 267         {
 268             ClassTypeSymbol* classType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(type);
 269             if (classType->Destructor())
 270             {
 271                 std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> destructorCall(new BoundFunctionCall(module, span, classType->Destructor()));
 272                 destructorCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(operatorFunCall->Arguments().back()->Clone()));
 273                 boundFunction->AddTemporaryDestructorCall(std::move(destructorCall));
 274             }
 275         }
 276     }
 277     expression.reset(operatorFunCall.release());
 278     if (temporary)
 279     {
 280         expression.reset(new BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression(module, std::move(expression),      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary))));
 281         expression->SetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::bindToRvalueReference);
 282     }
 283 }
 284 
 285 void ExpressionBinder::BindSymbol(Symbol* symbol, IdentifierNode* idNode)
 286 {
 287     switch (symbol->GetSymbolType())
 288     {
 289         case SymbolType::functionGroupSymbol:
 290         {
 291             FunctionGroupSymbol* functionGroupSymbol = static_cast<FunctionGroupSymbol*>(symbol);
 292             BoundFunctionGroupExpression* boundFunctionGroupExpression = new BoundFunctionGroupExpression(module, span, functionGroupSymbol);
 293             ParameterSymbol* thisParam = boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetThisParam();
 294             if (thisParam)
 295             {
 296                 boundFunctionGroupExpression->SetClassPtr(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(module, span, thisParam)));
 297             }
 298             expression.reset(boundFunctionGroupExpression);
 299             break;
 300         }
 301         case SymbolType::classTypeSymbol: case SymbolType::classTemplateSpecializationSymbol:
 302         {
 303             ClassTypeSymbol* classTypeSymbol = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 304             CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), classTypeSymbol);
 305             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, classTypeSymbol));
 306             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 307             {
 308                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, classTypeSymbol);
 309             }
 310             break;
 311         }
 312         case SymbolType::classGroupTypeSymbol:
 313         {
 314             ClassGroupTypeSymbol* classGroupTypeSymbol = static_cast<ClassGroupTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 315             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, classGroupTypeSymbol));
 316             ClassTypeSymbol* classTypeSymbol = classGroupTypeSymbol->GetClass(0);
 317             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc) && classTypeSymbol)
 318             {
 319                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, classTypeSymbol);
 320             }
 321             break;
 322         }
 323         case SymbolType::interfaceTypeSymbol:
 324         {
 325             InterfaceTypeSymbol* interfaceTypeSymbol = static_cast<InterfaceTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 326             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, interfaceTypeSymbol));
 327             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 328             {
 329                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, interfaceTypeSymbol);
 330             }
 331             break;
 332         }
 333         case SymbolType::delegateTypeSymbol:
 334         {
 335             DelegateTypeSymbol* delegateTypeSymbol = static_cast<DelegateTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 336             CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), delegateTypeSymbol);
 337             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, delegateTypeSymbol));
 338             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 339             {
 340                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, delegateTypeSymbol);
 341             }
 342             break;
 343         }
 344         case SymbolType::classDelegateTypeSymbol:
 345         {
 346             ClassDelegateTypeSymbol* classDelegateTypeSymbol = static_cast<ClassDelegateTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 347             CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), classDelegateTypeSymbol);
 348             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, classDelegateTypeSymbol));
 349             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 350             {
 351                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, classDelegateTypeSymbol);
 352             }
 353             break;
 354         }
 355         case SymbolType::typedefSymbol:
 356         {
 357             TypedefSymbol* typedefSymbol = static_cast<TypedefSymbol*>(symbol);
 358             CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), typedefSymbol);
 359             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, typedefSymbol->GetType()));
 360             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 361             {
 362                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, typedefSymbol);
 363             }
 364             break;
 365         }
 366         case SymbolType::boundTemplateParameterSymbol:
 367         {
 368             BoundTemplateParameterSymbol* boundTemplateParameterSymbol = static_cast<BoundTemplateParameterSymbol*>(symbol);
 369             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, boundTemplateParameterSymbol->GetType()));
 370             break;
 371         }
 372         case SymbolType::parameterSymbol:
 373         {
 374             ParameterSymbol* parameterSymbol = static_cast<ParameterSymbol*>(symbol);
 375             CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), parameterSymbol);
 376             expression.reset(new BoundParameter(module, span, parameterSymbol));
 377             break;
 378         }
 379         case SymbolType::localVariableSymbol:
 380         {
 381             LocalVariableSymbol* localVariableSymbol = static_cast<LocalVariableSymbol*>(symbol);
 382             CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), localVariableSymbol);
 383             expression.reset(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, localVariableSymbol));
 384             break;
 385         }
 386         case SymbolType::memberVariableSymbol:
 387         {
 388             MemberVariableSymbol* memberVariableSymbol = static_cast<MemberVariableSymbol*>(symbol);
 389             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 390             {
 391                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, memberVariableSymbol);
 392             }
 393             FunctionSymbol* currentFuctionSymbol = boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol();
 394             CheckAccess(currentFuctionSymbol, memberVariableSymbol);
 395             BoundMemberVariable* bmv = new BoundMemberVariable(module, span, memberVariableSymbol);
 396             bool accessFromOwnScope = false;
 397             ClassTypeSymbol* currentClass = currentFuctionSymbol->ContainingClassNoThrow();
 398             if (currentClass)
 399             {
 400                 ClassTypeSymbol* cp = memberVariableSymbol->ContainingClassNoThrow();
 401                 Assert(cp, "class type symbol expected");
 402                 if (cp == currentClass)
 403                 {
 404                     accessFromOwnScope = true;
 405                 }
 406             }
 407             if (memberVariableSymbol->IsStatic())
 408             {
 409                 if (!accessFromOwnScope)
 410                 {
 411                     bmv->SetStaticInitNeeded();
 412                 }
 413             }
 414             else
 415             {
 416                 ParameterSymbol* thisParam = currentFuctionSymbol->GetThisParam();
 417                 if (accessFromOwnScope && !currentFuctionSymbol->IsStatic())
 418                 {
 419                     if (thisParam)
 420                     {
 421                         TypeSymbol* thisPointerType = thisParam->GetType()->BaseType()->AddPointer(span);
 422                         if (thisParam->GetType()->IsConstType())
 423                         {
 424                             thisPointerType = thisPointerType->AddConst(span);
 425                         }
 426                         bmv->SetClassPtr(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(module, span, thisParam)));
 427                     }
 428                     else
 429                     {
 430                         Assert(false, "this param expected");
 431                     }
 432                 }
 433                 else if (thisParam)
 434                 {
 435                     ClassTypeSymbol* containingClass = memberVariableSymbol->ContainingClassNoThrow();
 436                     TypeSymbol* containingClassPointerType = containingClass->AddPointer(span);
 437                     TypeSymbol* thisPointerType = thisParam->GetType()->AddPointer(span);
 438                     if (thisParam->GetType()->IsConstType())
 439                     {
 440                         thisPointerType = thisPointerType->AddConst(span);
 441                         containingClassPointerType->AddConst(span);
 442                     }
 443                     ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
 444                     FunctionSymbol* conversionFun = boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(thisPointerType, containingClassPointerType, containerScope, boundFunction, span, argumentMatch);
 445                     if (conversionFun)
 446                     {
 447                         bmv->SetClassPtr(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundConversion(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(module, span, thisParam)), conversionFun)));
 448                     }
 449                 }
 450             }
 451             expression.reset(bmv);
 452             break;
 453         }
 454         case SymbolType::constantSymbol:
 455         {
 456             ConstantSymbol* constantSymbol = static_cast<ConstantSymbol*>(symbol);
 457             CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), constantSymbol);
 458             expression.reset(new BoundConstant(module, span, constantSymbol));
 459             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 460             {
 461                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, constantSymbol);
 462             }
 463             break;
 464         }
 465         case SymbolType::enumTypeSymbol:
 466         {
 467             EnumTypeSymbol* enumTypeSymbol = static_cast<EnumTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 468             CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), enumTypeSymbol);
 469             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, enumTypeSymbol));
 470             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 471             {
 472                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, enumTypeSymbol);
 473             }
 474             break;
 475         }
 476         case SymbolType::enumConstantSymbol:
 477         {
 478             EnumConstantSymbol* enumConstantSymbol = static_cast<EnumConstantSymbol*>(symbol);
 479             expression.reset(new BoundEnumConstant(module, span, enumConstantSymbol));
 480             if (idNode && GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 481             {
 482                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, enumConstantSymbol);
 483             }
 484             break;
 485         }
 486         case SymbolType::namespaceSymbol:
 487         {
 488             NamespaceSymbol* ns = static_cast<NamespaceSymbol*>(symbol);
 489             expression.reset(new BoundNamespaceExpression(module, span, ns));
 490             break;
 491         }
 492         default:
 493         {
 494             throw Exception(module, "could not bind '" + ToUtf8(symbol->FullName()) + "'", span, symbol->GetSpan());
 495         }
 496     }
 497 }

 674 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(IdentifierNode& identifierNode)
 675 {
 676     symbolTable.SetLatestIdentifier(&identifierNode);
 677     std::u32string name = identifierNode.Str();
 678     Symbol* symbol = containerScope->Lookup(name, ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent);
 679     if (!symbol)
 680     {
 681         for (const std::unique_ptr<FileScope>& fileScope : boundCompileUnit.FileScopes())
 682         {
 683             symbol = fileScope->Lookup(name);
 684             if (symbol)
 685             {
 686                 break;
 687             }
 688         }
 689     }
 690     if (symbol)
 691     {
 692         BindSymbol(symbol, &identifierNode);
 693     }
 694     else
 695     {
 696         throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' not found", identifierNode.GetSpan());
 697     }
 698 }

 700 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(TemplateIdNode& templateIdNode)
 701 {
 702     int arity = templateIdNode.TemplateArguments().Count();
 703     templateIdNode.Primary()->Accept(*this);
 704     if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundTypeExpression)
 705     {
 706         TypeSymbol* typeSymbol = expression->GetType();
 707         if (typeSymbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classGroupTypeSymbol)
 708         {
 709             ClassGroupTypeSymbol* classGroup = static_cast<ClassGroupTypeSymbol*>(typeSymbol);
 710             typeSymbol = classGroup->GetClass(arity);
 711             expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, typeSymbol));
 712         }
 713     }
 714     std::vector<TypeSymbol*> templateArgumentTypes;
 715     int n = arity;
 716     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 717     {
 718         Node* templateArgumentNode = templateIdNode.TemplateArguments()[i];
 719         TypeSymbol* type = ResolveType(templateArgumentNode, boundCompileUnit, containerScope);
 720         templateArgumentTypes.push_back(type);
 721     }
 722     if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundFunctionGroupExpression)
 723     {
 724         BoundFunctionGroupExpression* bfge = static_cast<BoundFunctionGroupExpression*>(expression.get());
 725         bfge->SetTemplateArgumentTypes(templateArgumentTypes);
 726     }
 727     else if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundMemberExpression)
 728     {
 729         BoundMemberExpression* bme = static_cast<BoundMemberExpression*>(expression.get());
 730         if (bme->Member()->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundFunctionGroupExpression)
 731         {
 732             BoundFunctionGroupExpression* bfge = static_cast<BoundFunctionGroupExpression*>(bme->Member());
 733             bfge->SetTemplateArgumentTypes(templateArgumentTypes);
 734         }
 735         else if (bme->Member()->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundTypeExpression)
 736         {
 737             TypeSymbol* typeSymbol = bme->Member()->GetType();
 738             if (typeSymbol->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 739             {
 740                 ClassTypeSymbol* classTypeSymbol = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(typeSymbol);
 741                 if (classTypeSymbol->IsClassTemplate())
 742                 {
 743                     int m = classTypeSymbol->TemplateParameters().size();
 744                     if (n < m)
 745                     {
 746                         boundCompileUnit.GetClassTemplateRepository().ResolveDefaultTemplateArguments(templateArgumentTypes, classTypeSymbol, containerScope, templateIdNode.GetSpan());
 747                     }
 748                     ClassTemplateSpecializationSymbol* classTemplateSpecialization = symbolTable.MakeClassTemplateSpecialization(classTypeSymbol, templateArgumentTypes, templateIdNode.GetSpan());
 749                     if (!classTemplateSpecialization->IsBound())
 750                     {
 751                         boundCompileUnit.GetClassTemplateRepository().BindClassTemplateSpecialization(classTemplateSpecialization, containerScope, templateIdNode.GetSpan());
 752                     }
 753                     expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, classTemplateSpecialization));
 754                 }
 755             }
 756         }
 757         else
 758         {
 759             throw Exception(module, "function group or class group expected", templateIdNode.GetSpan());
 760         }
 761     }
 762     else if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundTypeExpression)
 763     {
 764         TypeSymbol* typeSymbol = expression->GetType();
 765         if (typeSymbol->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 766         {
 767             ClassTypeSymbol* classTypeSymbol = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(typeSymbol);
 768             if (classTypeSymbol->IsClassTemplate())
 769             {
 770                 int m = classTypeSymbol->TemplateParameters().size();
 771                 if (n < m)
 772                 {
 773                     boundCompileUnit.GetClassTemplateRepository().ResolveDefaultTemplateArguments(templateArgumentTypes, classTypeSymbol, containerScope, templateIdNode.GetSpan());
 774                 }
 775                 ClassTemplateSpecializationSymbol* classTemplateSpecialization = symbolTable.MakeClassTemplateSpecialization(classTypeSymbol, templateArgumentTypes, templateIdNode.GetSpan());
 776                 if (!classTemplateSpecialization->IsBound())
 777                 {
 778                     boundCompileUnit.GetClassTemplateRepository().BindClassTemplateSpecialization(classTemplateSpecialization, containerScope, templateIdNode.GetSpan());
 779                 }
 780                 expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, classTemplateSpecialization));
 781             }
 782         }
 783     }
 784     else
 785     {
 786         throw Exception(module, "function group or class group expected", templateIdNode.GetSpan());
 787     }
 788 }
 789 
 790 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(ParameterNode& parameterNode)
 791 {
 792     if (!parameterNode.Id())
 793     {
 794         throw Exception(module, "parameter not named", parameterNode.GetSpan());
 795     }
 796     std::u32string name = parameterNode.Id()->Str();
 797     Symbol* symbol = containerScope->Lookup(name, ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent);
 798     if (!symbol)
 799     {
 800         for (const std::unique_ptr<FileScope>& fileScope : boundCompileUnit.FileScopes())
 801         {
 802             symbol = fileScope->Lookup(name);
 803             if (symbol)
 804             {
 805                 break;
 806             }
 807         }
 808     }
 809     if (symbol)
 810     {
 811         if (symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::parameterSymbol)
 812         {
 813             ParameterSymbol* parameterSymbol = static_cast<ParameterSymbol*>(symbol);
 814             expression.reset(new BoundParameter(module, span, parameterSymbol));
 815         }
 816         else
 817         {
 818             throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' does not denote a parameter", parameterNode.GetSpan());
 819         }
 820     }
 821     else
 822     {
 823         throw Exception(module, "parameter symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' not found", parameterNode.GetSpan());
 824     }
 825 }
 826 
 827 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(DotNode& dotNode)
 828 {
 829     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 830     expression = BindExpression(dotNode.Subject(), boundCompileUnit, boundFunction, containerScope, statementBinder, false, true, true, false);
 831     IdentifierNode* idNode = symbolTable.GetLatestIdentifier();
 832     symbolTable.SetLatestIdentifier(dotNode.MemberId());
 833     if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundTypeExpression)
 834     {
 835         TypeSymbol* typeSymbol = expression->GetType();
 836         if (typeSymbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classGroupTypeSymbol)
 837         {
 838             ClassGroupTypeSymbol* classGroupTypeSymbol = static_cast<ClassGroupTypeSymbol*>(typeSymbol);
 839             typeSymbol = classGroupTypeSymbol->GetClass(0);
 840             if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 841             {
 842                 symbolTable.MapSymbol(idNode, typeSymbol);
 843             }
 844             if (!typeSymbol)
 845             {
 846                 throw Exception(module, "ordinary class not found from class group '" + ToUtf8(classGroupTypeSymbol->FullName()) + "'", span, classGroupTypeSymbol->GetSpan());
 847             }
 848             else
 849             {
 850                 expression.reset(new BoundTypeExpression(module, span, typeSymbol));
 851             }
 852         }
 853     }
 854     if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundNamespaceExpression)
 855     {
 856         BoundNamespaceExpression* bns = static_cast<BoundNamespaceExpression*>(expression.get());
 857         containerScope = bns->Ns()->GetContainerScope();
 858         std::u32string name = dotNode.MemberId()->Str();
 859         Symbol* symbol = containerScope->Lookup(name, ScopeLookup::this_);
 860         if (symbol)
 861         {
 862             BindSymbol(symbol, dotNode.MemberId());
 863             if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundFunctionGroupExpression)
 864             {
 865                 BoundFunctionGroupExpression* bfe = static_cast<BoundFunctionGroupExpression*>(expression.get());
 866                 bfe->SetScopeQualified();
 867                 bfe->SetQualifiedScope(containerScope);
 868             }
 869         }
 870         else
 871         {
 872             throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' not found from namespace '" + ToUtf8(bns->Ns()->FullName()) + "'", dotNode.MemberId()->GetSpan());
 873         }
 874     }
 875     else
 876     {
 877         TypeSymbol* type = expression->GetType()->PlainType(dotNode.GetSpan());
 878         if (type->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 879         {
 880             ClassTypeSymbol* classType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(type->BaseType());
 881             ContainerScope* scope = classType->GetContainerScope();
 882             std::u32string name = dotNode.MemberId()->Str();
 883             Symbol* symbol = scope->Lookup(name, ScopeLookup::this_and_base);
 884             if (symbol)
 885             {
 886                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> classPtr;
 887                 BoundExpression* plainClassPtr = expression.get();
 888                 if (expression->GetType()->IsClassTypeSymbol())
 889                 {
 890                     TypeSymbol* type = expression->GetType()->AddPointer(dotNode.GetSpan());
 891                     classPtr.reset(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(expression.release()), type));
 892                 }
 893                 else if (expression->GetType()->IsReferenceType())
 894                 {
 895                     TypeSymbol* type = expression->GetType()->RemoveReference(dotNode.GetSpan())->AddPointer(dotNode.GetSpan());
 896                     classPtr.reset(new BoundReferenceToPointerExpression(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(expression.release()), type));
 897                 }
 898                 else
 899                 {
 900                     classPtr.reset(expression.release());
 901                 }
 902                 BindSymbol(symbol, dotNode.MemberId());
 903                 if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundFunctionGroupExpression)
 904                 {
 905                     BoundFunctionGroupExpression* bfg = static_cast<BoundFunctionGroupExpression*>(expression.get());
 906                     if (!classPtr->GetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr))
 907                     {
 908                         Symbol* parent = symbol->Parent();
 909                         Assert(parent->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTypeSymbol || parent->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTemplateSpecializationSymbol, "class type expected");
 910                         ClassTypeSymbol* owner = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(parent);
 911                         if (classType->HasBaseClass(owner))
 912                         {
 913                             if (classPtr->GetType()->IsConstType())
 914                             {
 915                                 ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
 916                                 classPtr.reset(new BoundConversion(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(classPtr.release()), 
 917                                     boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(classType->AddConst(span)->AddPointer(span), owner->AddConst(span)->AddPointer(span), containerScope, boundFunction, dotNode.GetSpan(), argumentMatch)));
 918                             }
 919                             else
 920                             {
 921                                 ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
 922                                 classPtr.reset(new BoundConversion(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(classPtr.release()), 
 923                                     boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(classType->AddPointer(span), owner->AddPointer(span), containerScope, boundFunction, dotNode.GetSpan(), argumentMatch)));
 924                             }
 925                         }
 926                     }
 927                     if (plainClassPtr->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundTypeExpression)
 928                     {
 929                         BoundTypeExpression* bte = static_cast<BoundTypeExpression*>(plainClassPtr);
 930                         bfg->SetScopeQualified();
 931                         bfg->SetQualifiedScope(bte->GetType()->GetContainerScope());
 932                     }
 933                     BoundMemberExpression* bme = new BoundMemberExpression(module, dotNode.GetSpan(),      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(classPtr.release()), std::move(expression));
 934                     expression.reset(bme);
 935                 }
 936                 else if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundMemberVariable)
 937                 {
 938                     BoundMemberVariable* bmv = static_cast<BoundMemberVariable*>(expression.get());
 939                     if (!bmv->GetMemberVariableSymbol()->IsStatic())
 940                     {
 941                         Symbol* parent = symbol->Parent();
 942                         Assert(parent->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTypeSymbol || parent->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTemplateSpecializationSymbol, "class type expected");
 943                         ClassTypeSymbol* owner = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(parent);
 944                         if (classType->HasBaseClass(owner))
 945                         {
 946                             if (classPtr->GetType()->IsConstType())
 947                             {
 948                                 ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
 949                                 classPtr.reset(new BoundConversion(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(classPtr.release()), 
 950                                     boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(classType->AddConst(span)->AddPointer(span), owner->AddConst(span)->AddPointer(span), containerScope, boundFunction, dotNode.GetSpan(), argumentMatch)));
 951                             }
 952                             else
 953                             {
 954                                 ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
 955                                 classPtr.reset(new BoundConversion(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(classPtr.release()), 
 956                                     boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(classType->AddPointer(span), owner->AddPointer(span), containerScope, boundFunction, dotNode.GetSpan(), argumentMatch)));
 957                             }
 958                         }
 959                         bmv->SetClassPtr(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(classPtr.release()));
 960                     }
 961                 }
 962                 else if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() != BoundNodeType::boundTypeExpression)
 963                 {
 964                     throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' does not denote a function group, member variable, or type", dotNode.MemberId()->GetSpan());
 965                 }
 966             }
 967             else
 968             {
 969                 throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' not found from class '" + ToUtf8(classType->FullName()) + "'", dotNode.MemberId()->GetSpan());
 970             }
 971         }
 972         else if (type->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::interfaceTypeSymbol)
 973         {
 974             InterfaceTypeSymbol* interfaceType = static_cast<InterfaceTypeSymbol*>(type->BaseType());
 975             ContainerScope* scope = interfaceType->GetContainerScope();
 976             std::u32string name = dotNode.MemberId()->Str();
 977             Symbol* symbol = scope->Lookup(name, ScopeLookup::this_);
 978             if (symbol)
 979             {
 980                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> interfacePtr;
 981                 interfacePtr.reset(expression.release());
 982                 BindSymbol(symbol, dotNode.MemberId());
 983                 if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundFunctionGroupExpression)
 984                 {
 985                     BoundFunctionGroupExpression* bfg = static_cast<BoundFunctionGroupExpression*>(expression.get());
 986                     BoundMemberExpression* bme = new BoundMemberExpression(module, dotNode.GetSpan(),      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(interfacePtr.release()), std::move(expression));
 987                     expression.reset(bme);
 988                 }
 989                 else
 990                 {
 991                     throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' does not denote a function group", dotNode.MemberId()->GetSpan());
 992                 }
 993             }
 994             else
 995             {
 996                 throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' not found from interface '" + ToUtf8(interfaceType->FullName()) + "'", dotNode.MemberId()->GetSpan());
 997             }
 998         }
 999         else if (type->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::enumTypeSymbol)
1000         {
1001             EnumTypeSymbol* enumType = static_cast<EnumTypeSymbol*>(type);
1002             ContainerScope* scope = enumType->GetContainerScope();
1003             std::u32string name = dotNode.MemberId()->Str();
1004             Symbol* symbol = scope->Lookup(name);
1005             if (symbol)
1006             {
1007                 BindSymbol(symbol, dotNode.MemberId());
1008             }
1009             else
1010             {
1011                 throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' not found from enumerated type '" + ToUtf8(enumType->FullName()) + "'", dotNode.MemberId()->GetSpan());
1012             }
1013         }
1014         else if (type->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::arrayTypeSymbol)
1015         {
1016             ArrayTypeSymbol* arrayType = static_cast<ArrayTypeSymbol*>(type);
1017             ContainerScope* scope = arrayType->GetContainerScope();
1018             std::u32string name = dotNode.MemberId()->Str();
1019             Symbol* symbol = scope->Lookup(name);
1020             if (symbol)
1021             {
1022                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> receiverPtr = std::move(expression);
1023                 BindSymbol(symbol, dotNode.MemberId());
1024                 if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundFunctionGroupExpression)
1025                 {
1026                     BoundFunctionGroupExpression* bfe = static_cast<BoundFunctionGroupExpression*>(expression.get());
1027                     bfe->SetScopeQualified();
1028                     bfe->SetQualifiedScope(scope);
1029                     bfe->SetClassPtr(std::move(receiverPtr));
1030                 }
1031             }
1032             else
1033             {
1034                 throw Exception(module, "symbol '" + ToUtf8(name) + "' not found from array type '" + ToUtf8(arrayType->FullName()) + "'", dotNode.MemberId()->GetSpan());
1035             }
1036         }
1037         else
1038         {
1039             throw Exception(module, "expression must denote a namespace, class type, interface type, array type or an enumerated type type object", dotNode.GetSpan());
1040         }
1041     }
1042     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1043 }

1083                     expression.reset(bme);
1084                 }

1093                         if (classType->HasBaseClass(owner))

1095                             if (classPtr->GetType()->IsConstType())
1096                             {

1100                             }
1101                             else
1102                             {
1103                                 ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
1104                                 classPtr.reset(new BoundConversion(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(classPtr.release()), 
1105                                     boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(classType->AddPointer(span), owner->AddPointer(span), containerScope, boundFunction, node.GetSpan(), argumentMatch)));
1106                             }
1107                         }

1109                     }
1110                     else

1112                         throw Exception(module, "member variable '" + ToUtf8(bmv->GetMemberVariableSymbol()->FullName()) + +"' is static", node.GetSpan());
1113                     }
1114                 }
1115                 else
1116                 {

1118                 }
1119             }
1120             else
1121             {

1123             }
1124         }
1125         else
1126         {

1134         LocalVariableSymbol* temporary = boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->CreateTemporary(type, node.GetSpan());

1137         boundFunctionCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary)), pointerType)));

1149             new BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression(module, std::move(expression),      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary)))), pointerType));

1159 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(ArrowNode& arrowNode)
1160 {
1161     arrowNode.Subject()->Accept(*this);
1162     bool argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr = expression->GetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr);
1163     if (expression->GetType()->IsReferenceType() && expression->GetType()->PlainType(arrowNode.GetSpan())->IsClassTypeSymbol())
1164     {
1165         TypeSymbol* type = expression->GetType()->RemoveReference(arrowNode.GetSpan())->AddPointer(arrowNode.GetSpan());
1166         expression.reset(new BoundReferenceToPointerExpression(module, std::move(expression), type));
1167     }
1168     else if (expression->GetType()->IsReferenceType())
1169     {
1170         TypeSymbol* type = expression->GetType()->RemoveReference(arrowNode.GetSpan())->AddPointer(arrowNode.GetSpan());
1171         expression.reset(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(expression), type)), type->AddPointer(arrowNode.GetSpan())));
1172     }
1173     else
1174     {
1175         TypeSymbol* type = expression->GetType()->AddPointer(arrowNode.GetSpan());
1176         expression.reset(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(expression), type));
1177     }
1178     BindUnaryOp(expression.release(), arrowNode, U"operator->");
1179     if (argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr)
1180     {
1181         expression->SetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr);
1182     }
1183     BindArrow(arrowNode, arrowNode.MemberId()->Str());
1184     if (argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr)
1185     {
1186         expression->SetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr);
1187     }
1188     symbolTable.SetLatestIdentifier(arrowNode.MemberId());
1189 }

1317 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(PrefixIncrementNode& prefixIncrementNode)
1318 {
1319     if (statementBinder->CompilingThrow())
1320     {
1321         throw Exception(module, "prefix increment in throw expression no allowed", prefixIncrementNode.GetSpan());
1322     }
1323     prefixIncrementNode.Subject()->Accept(*this);
1324     if (expression->GetType()->PlainType(prefixIncrementNode.GetSpan())->IsClassTypeSymbol())
1325     {
1326         BindUnaryOp(prefixIncrementNode, U"operator++");
1327     }
1328     else
1329     {
1330         if (!inhibitCompile)
1331         {
1332             if (expression->GetType()->IsUnsignedType())
1333             {

1599 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(InvokeNode& invokeNode)
1600 {
1601     IdentifierNode* prevIdentifier = symbolTable.GetLatestIdentifier();
1602     invokeNode.Subject()->Accept(*this);
1603     IdentifierNode* invokeId = symbolTable.GetLatestIdentifier();
1604     symbolTable.SetLatestIdentifier(prevIdentifier);
1605     bool argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr = expression->GetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::argIsExplicitThisOrBasePtr);
1606     std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> arguments;
1607     std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
1608     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
1609     FunctionGroupSymbol* functionGroupSymbol = nullptr;

1623             functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_, bfge->QualifiedScope()));
1624             scopeQualified = true;
1625             if (bfge->ClassPtr())
1626             {
1627                 arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(bfge->ReleaseClassPtr()));
1628             }
1629         }
1630     }
1631     else if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundMemberExpression)
1632     {
1633         BoundMemberExpression* bme = static_cast<BoundMemberExpression*>(expression.get());
1634         if (bme->Member()->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundFunctionGroupExpression)
1635         {
1636             BoundFunctionGroupExpression* bfge = static_cast<BoundFunctionGroupExpression*>(bme->Member());
1637             functionGroupSymbol = bfge->FunctionGroup();
1638             templateArgumentTypes = bfge->TemplateArgumentTypes();
1639             groupName = functionGroupSymbol->Name();
1640             if (bfge->IsScopeQualified())
1641             {
1642                 functionScopeLookups.clear();
1643                 functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_, bfge->QualifiedScope()));
1644                 scopeQualified = true;
1645             }
1646             if (!scopeQualified)
1647             {
1648                 functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base, bme->ClassPtr()->GetType()->BaseType()->ClassInterfaceOrNsScope()));
1649             }
1650             arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(bme->ReleaseClassPtr()));
1651             if (arguments.front()->GetType()->PlainType(span)->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::interfaceTypeSymbol)
1652             {
1653                 if (arguments.front()->GetType()->IsReferenceType())
1654                 {
1655                     TypeSymbol* type = arguments.front()->GetType()->RemoveReference(span)->AddPointer(span);
1656                     arguments[0].reset(new BoundReferenceToPointerExpression(module, std::move(arguments[0]), type));
1657                 }
1658                 else
1659                 {
1660                     TypeSymbol* type = arguments.front()->GetType()->AddPointer(span);

1662                 }
1663             }
1664         }
1665         else
1666         {
1667             throw Exception(module, "invoke cannot be applied to this type of expression", invokeNode.Subject()->GetSpan());
1668         }
1669     }
1670     else if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundTypeExpression)
1671     {

1673         if (type->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classGroupTypeSymbol)

1682             type = classTypeSymbol;
1683         }
1684         if (!scopeQualified)
1685         {

1709         if (type->IsReferenceType())

1712         }

1718     }

1725         }

1727         {
1728             arguments.push_back(std::move(expression));
1729         }

1731         int n = invokeNode.Arguments().Count();
1732         if (n != delegateTypeSymbol->Arity())
1733         {
1734             throw Exception(module, "wrong number of arguments for calling delegate type '" + ToUtf8(delegateTypeSymbol->FullName()) + "'", span);
1735         }

1740             argument->Accept(*this);

1742             if (!TypesEqual(argumentType, delegateParameterType))

1750                         expression.reset(dereferenceExpression);
1751                     }

1753                     {

1756                         expression.reset(addressOfExpression);
1757                     }

1763                     if (conversionFun)

1778         for (std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>& argument : arguments)

1781         }

1786             temporary = boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->CreateTemporary(type, invokeNode.GetSpan());
1787             delegateCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary)), 
1788                 type->AddPointer(invokeNode.GetSpan()))));
1789             if (type->IsClassTypeSymbol())

2237     FunctionMatch functionMatch(castFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
2238     bool conversionFound = FindConversions(boundCompileUnit, castFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol(), castArguments, functionMatch, ConversionType::explicit_, containerScope, boundFunction, 
2239         castNode.GetSpan());
2240     if (conversionFound)
2241     {
2242         Assert(!functionMatch.argumentMatches.empty(), "argument match expected");
2243         ArgumentMatch& argumentMatch = functionMatch.argumentMatches[0];
2244         if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags != OperationFlags::none)
2245         {
2246             if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::addr)
2247             {
2248                 TypeSymbol* type = castArguments[0]->GetType()->AddLvalueReference(span);
2249                 BoundAddressOfExpression* addressOfExpression = new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(castArguments[0]), type);
2250                 castArguments[0].reset(addressOfExpression);
2251             }
2252             else if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::deref)
2253             {
2254                 TypeSymbol* type = castArguments[0]->GetType()->RemoveReference(span);
2255                 BoundDereferenceExpression* dereferenceExpression = new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(castArguments[0]), type);
2256                 castArguments[0].reset(dereferenceExpression);
2257             }
2258         }
2259         FunctionSymbol* conversionFun = argumentMatch.conversionFun;
2260         if (conversionFun)
2261         {
2262             if (conversionFun->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::constructorSymbol)
2263             {
2264                 BoundFunctionCall* constructorCall = new BoundFunctionCall(module, span, conversionFun);
2265                 LocalVariableSymbol* temporary = boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->CreateTemporary(conversionFun->ConversionTargetType(), span);
2266                 constructorCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary)), 
2267                     conversionFun->ConversionTargetType()->AddPointer(span))));
2268                 TypeSymbol* conversionTargetType = conversionFun->ConversionTargetType();
2269                 if (conversionTargetType->IsClassTypeSymbol())
2270                 {
2271                     ClassTypeSymbol* classType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(conversionTargetType);
2272                     if (classType->Destructor())
2273                     {
2274                         std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> destructorCall(new BoundFunctionCall(module, span, classType->Destructor()));
2275                         destructorCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(constructorCall->Arguments()[0]->Clone()));
2276                         boundFunction->AddTemporaryDestructorCall(std::move(destructorCall));
2277                     }
2278                 }
2279                 constructorCall->AddArgument(std::move(castArguments[0]));
2280                 BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression* conversion = new BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(constructorCall), 
2281                          std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, span, temporary)));
2282                 castArguments[0].reset(conversion);
2283             }
2284             else
2285             {
2286                 castArguments[0].reset(new BoundConversion(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(castArguments[0].release()), conversionFun));
2287             }
2288         }
2289         if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags != OperationFlags::none)
2290         {
2291             if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::addr)
2292             {
2293                 TypeSymbol* type = castArguments[0]->GetType()->AddLvalueReference(span);
2294                 BoundAddressOfExpression* addressOfExpression = new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(castArguments[0]), type);
2295                 castArguments[0].reset(addressOfExpression);
2296             }
2297             else if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::deref)
2298             {
2299                 TypeSymbol* type = castArguments[0]->GetType()->RemoveReference(span);
2300                 BoundDereferenceExpression* dereferenceExpression = new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(castArguments[0]), type);
2301                 castArguments[0].reset(dereferenceExpression);
2302             }
2303         }
2304         castFunctionCall->SetArguments(std::move(castArguments));
2305     }
2306     else
2307     {
2308         throw Exception(module, "no explicit conversion from '" + ToUtf8(castArguments[0]->GetType()->FullName()) + "' to '" + ToUtf8(targetType->FullName()) + "' exists", 
2309             castNode.GetSpan(), boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
2310     }
2311     CheckAccess(boundFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), castFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
2312     expression.reset(castFunctionCall.release());
2313 }

2315 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(ConstructNode& constructNode)
2316 {
2317     TypeSymbol* resultType = nullptr;
2318     int n = constructNode.Arguments().Count();
2319     if (n == 0)
2320     {
2321         throw Exception(module, "must supply at least one argument to construct expression", constructNode.GetSpan());
2322     }
2323     std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> arguments;
2324     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
2325     {
2326         Node* argumentNode = constructNode.Arguments()[i];
2327         if (i == 0)
2328         {
2329             CloneContext cloneContext;
2330             CastNode castNode(constructNode.GetSpan(), new PointerNode(constructNode.GetSpan(), constructNode.TypeExpr()->Clone(cloneContext)), argumentNode->Clone(cloneContext));
2331             castNode.Accept(*this);
2332             resultType = expression->GetType();
2333             if (!resultType->IsPointerType())
2334             {
2335                 throw Exception(module, "first argument of a construct expression must be of a pointer type", argumentNode->GetSpan());
2336             }
2337             if (!resultType->RemovePointer(constructNode.GetSpan())->IsClassTypeSymbol())
2338             {
2339                 expression->SetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::deref);
2340             }
2341         }
2342         else
2343         {
2344             argumentNode->Accept(*this);
2345         }
2346         arguments.push_back(std::move(expression));
2347     }
2348     std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
2349     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
2350     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, resultType->RemovePointer(constructNode.GetSpan())->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
2351     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
2352     expression = ResolveOverload(U"@constructor", containerScope, functionScopeLookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, boundFunction, constructNode.GetSpan());
2353     expression.reset(new BoundConstructExpression(module, std::move(expression), resultType));
2354 }

2356 void ExpressionBinder::Visit(NewNode& newNode)
2357 {
2358     CloneContext cloneContext;
2359     InvokeNode* invokeMemAlloc = nullptr;
2360     bool memDebug = boundCompileUnit.GetModule().IsSymbolDefined(U"MEM_DEBUG");
2361     if (memDebug)
2362     {
2363         invokeMemAlloc = new InvokeNode(newNode.GetSpan(), new IdentifierNode(newNode.GetSpan(), U"RtMemAllocInfo"));
2364     }
2365     else
2366     {
2367         invokeMemAlloc = new InvokeNode(newNode.GetSpan(), new IdentifierNode(newNode.GetSpan(), U"RtMemAlloc"));
2368     }
2369     invokeMemAlloc->AddArgument(new SizeOfNode(newNode.GetSpan(), newNode.TypeExpr()->Clone(cloneContext)));
2370     if (memDebug)
2371     {
2372         TypeNameNode* typeNameNode = new TypeNameNode(newNode.GetSpan(), newNode.TypeExpr()->Clone(cloneContext));
2373         typeNameNode->SetStatic();
2374         invokeMemAlloc->AddArgument(typeNameNode);
2375     }
2376     CastNode castNode(newNode.GetSpan(), new PointerNode(newNode.GetSpan(), newNode.TypeExpr()->Clone(cloneContext)), invokeMemAlloc);
2377     castNode.Accept(*this);
2378     std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> arguments;
2379     TypeSymbol* resultType = expression->GetType();
2380     if (!resultType->RemovePointer(newNode.GetSpan())->IsClassTypeSymbol())
2381     {
2382         expression->SetFlag(BoundExpressionFlags::deref);
2383     }
2384     arguments.push_back(std::move(expression));
2385     int n = newNode.Arguments().Count();
2386     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
2387     {
2388         newNode.Arguments()[i]->Accept(*this);
2389         arguments.push_back(std::move(expression));
2390     }
2391     std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
2392     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
2393     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, resultType->RemovePointer(newNode.GetSpan())->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
2394     functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
2395     expression = ResolveOverload(U"@constructor", containerScope, functionScopeLookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, boundFunction, newNode.GetSpan());
2396     expression.reset(new BoundConstructExpression(module, std::move(expression), resultType));
2397 }

2484 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> BindExpression(Node* node, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit, BoundFunction* boundFunction, ContainerScope* containerScope, StatementBinder* statementBinder, bool lvalue, 
2485     bool acceptFunctionGroupOrMemberExpression, bool acceptIncomplete, bool moveTemporaryDestructorCalls)
2486 {
2487     ExpressionBinder expressionBinder(node->GetSpan(), boundCompileUnit, boundFunction, containerScope, statementBinder, lvalue);
2488     node->Accept(expressionBinder);
2489     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> expression = expressionBinder.GetExpression();
2490     if (!expression)
2491     {
2492         throw Exception(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule(), "could not bind expression", node->GetSpan());
2493     }
2494     if (moveTemporaryDestructorCalls)
2495     {
2496         boundFunction->MoveTemporaryDestructorCallsTo(*expression);
2497     }
2498     if (acceptFunctionGroupOrMemberExpression && (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundFunctionGroupExpression || expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundMemberExpression))
2499     {
2500         return expression;
2501     }
2502     if (!acceptIncomplete)
2503     {
2504         if (!expression->IsComplete())
2505         {
2506             throw Exception(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule(), "incomplete expression", node->GetSpan());
2507         }
2508     }
2509     if (lvalue && !expression->IsLvalueExpression())
2510     {
2511         throw Exception(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule(), "not an lvalue expression", node->GetSpan());
2512     }
2513     return expression;
2514 }
